article.headline: Idaho 78, N. Dakota St. 69
article.story: MOSCOW, Idaho -- With Kashif Watshon leading the way with 19 points, Idaho overcame a 43-38 halftime deficit to beat North Dakota State 78-69 Saturday night. Watshon also had six rebounds and six steals, while Mac Hopson had 11 points and eight assists for the Vandals (1-2). Hopson, Idaho's point guard, made only one turnover. The Bison (1-1) looked to be in control of the game until the midway point of the second half when the Vandals began to wear them down. Idaho tied the score at 62 on a 3-pointer by Hopson with 8:25 left. The Bison were led by Brett Winkelman and Mike Nelson, who each scored 17 points. Marvin Jefferson scored 16 points and Luciano de Souza 15 for Idaho.
